{{Pizza}} '''National pizza month''' is an American observance that occurs for the month of October every year.
==History== This observance began in October 1984, and was created by Gerry Durnell, the publisher of ''[[Pizza Today]]'' magazine.<ref name="NPM"/> Some people observe National pizza month by consuming various types of [[pizza]]s or pizza slices, or going to various pizzerias.<ref name="Genovese"/> During the month, some [[pizzerias]] give away free pizzas or pizza slices to customers or offer reduced-price promotions.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pmq.com/October-2014/Pie-Five-Pies-It-Forward-For-National-Pizza-Month/|title=Pie Five Pizza pays it forward|publisher=PMQ Pizza Magazine|accessdate=16 October 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.myfoxdc.com/story/26685710/pizza-restaurant-gives-away-free-pies-in-honor-of-national-pizza-month|title=Pizza restaurant gives away free pies in honor of National Pizza|date=2 October 2014|publisher=DC News FOX 5|accessdate=16 October 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.myfoxdetroit.com/story/23598725/happys-pizza-celebrating-national-pizza-month|title=Happy's Pizza celebrating National Pizza Month|date=3 October 2013|publisher=|accessdate=16 October 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pmq.com/September-2014/Dominos-Pizza-to-Offer-Weeklong-Carryout-Special-Just-in-Time-for-National-Pizza-Month/|title=Domino's has deal for national pizza month|publisher=PMQ Pizza Magazine|accessdate=16 October 2014}}</ref> Some businesses run fundraising drives, donating proceeds of pizza sales to benefit various organizations or charities.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pmq.com/October-2012/Pizza-Pizza-Closes-National-Pizza-Month-With-Fundraiser-for-Childrens-Miracle-Network/|title=Pizza Pizza Closes National Pizza Month With Fundraiser for Children's Miracle Network|publisher=PMQ Pizza Magazine|accessdate=16 October 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ODgtAQAAMAAJ&q=%22National+pizza+month%22+fundraiser&dq=%22National+pizza+month%22+fundraiser&hl=en&sa=X&ei=3C0_VOKZCMHCigLr3IGQBA&ved=0CDAQ6AEwAA|title=Pizza Today|publisher=Pizza Today|accessdate=16 October 2014|pages=8, 38}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.restaurantnews.com/old-chicago-pizza-taproom-donating-1-from-select-specialty-pizzas-to-benefit-childrens-hospital-medical-center-this-month/|date=October 14, 2014|title=Old Chicago Pizza & Taproom Donating $1 From Select Specialty Pizzas To Benefit Children’s Hospital & Medical Center This Month|work=|accessdate=16 October 2014|publisher=Restaurant News}}</ref> Some pizzerias create unique pizzas that they don't routinely offer. For example, Mamma Mia! Pizza Kitchen in [[Levelland, Texas]] created a pizza prepared with [[rattlesnake]] meat in 2009 to celebrate the month.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pmq.com/October-2009/National-Pizza-Month-Calls-For-a-Rattlesnake-Round-Up/|title=National Pizza Month Calls For a Rattlesnake Round-Up|publisher= PMQ Pizza Magazine|accessdate=16 October 2014}}</ref>
